The U.S. Treasury Department
announced Michael Hirson, a former senior associate in  emerging
markets  and international affairs at the Federal Reserve Bank of
New York, will be its attache in Beijing.  Marisa Lago, assistant secretary for international markets
and development, made the announcement in an e-mailed statement
today.  Before the New York Fed, Hirson worked as a Treasury desk
officer for China, Mongolia, Egypt, Israel and the West
Bank/Gaza and was the departmentâ€™s attache in Kabul. Most
recently he was deputy director of the  Middle East  and North
Africa office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
